25/04/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Sali Berisha was re-elected leader of the major opposition Democratic Party (DP) during the party congress Sunday (24 April) evening, according to media reports from the region. Berisha, a former Albanian president, was the sole candidate for the position. Addressing delegates in congress, he said he expects a strong showing from DP in the parliamentary elections this summer. He plans to become prime minister in the case of an outright DP victory. (HINA, Makfax - 25/04/05)
